<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Log into the admin portal</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Open the admin portal</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Open the <code>AdminPortalUrl</code> from the CloudFormation outputs in a new tab. Enter the <code>AdminUsername</code> and <code>AdminPassword</code> to log in.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Explore the dashboard</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      The admin dashboard shows an overview of the system:
    </p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li><strong>Fund summaries</strong> — totals across the 10 council funds</li>
      <li><strong>Recent transactions</strong> — the latest payments and adjustments</li>
      <li><strong>Suspense items</strong> — payments awaiting allocation (you'll explore these in Step 3)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Search for an account</h3>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number govuk-list--spaced">
  <li>
    <strong>Use the account search</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Navigate to the account search. Try searching for the same account you used in Step 1 (for example, <code>CT-001</code> or the account holder name).
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>View the account details</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Click on an account to see its full details:
    </p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li><strong>Account holder</strong> — name, address, and contact details</li>
      <li><strong>Fund allocation</strong> — which council fund this account belongs to</li>
      <li><strong>Balance</strong> — current amount outstanding</li>
      <li><strong>Transaction history</strong> — all payments, adjustments, and charges</li>
    </ul>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>Find your payment from Step 1</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Scroll through the transaction history. You should see the payment you made via GOV.UK Pay in the previous step, with a GOV.UK Pay reference number and today's date.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <strong>View a receipt</strong>
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Click on the transaction to view the full receipt details. This shows:
    </p>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li><strong>Payment method</strong> — GOV.UK Pay card payment</li>
      <li><strong>Amount</strong> — the payment amount</li>
      <li><strong>Reference</strong> — the GOV.UK Pay transaction reference</li>
      <li><strong>Timestamp</strong> — when the payment was processed</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

